data.title: Sophisticated dining for all occasions
data.text: The Grant Grill is a hidden gem tucked away off the elegant lobby of The US Grant Hotel. From hearty breakfasts to delicious lunches to afternoon indulgences to elegant dinner to lively music and drinks, this dining spot has something for everyone. The service is impeccable, the food is cooked to order and delicious, and if you're lucky, the in-house master mixologist will craft a special cocktail for you.

data.title: Always Fine Dining, always surprisingly innovative
data.text:
I had Mr. Alberto's special fall Apple Harvest festival tasting menu $82 with the optional wine and drink pairings. $39, 

Chef Mark Kropczynski has a well-earned reputation for excellence.

This was an expensive meal, but if you're looking for a gourmet dining experience, the price is well worth it. 

The service is always friendly, and the food is always amazing. The specialty drinks are amazing. Alberto keeps on satisfying his customers, and he has a loyal following.

I like that I can have a 5-course meal at the Grant Grill and will not feel stuffed. For me the serving portions are just right.

The bar is very popular in itself for happy hour drinks and snacks. I wouldn't consider a visit to San Diego complete without a stop at the Grant Grill. Don't miss it.

data.title: Great Place for cocktails
data.text: We stayed at the hotel that is attached to this establishment. They have an amazing cocktail list and great service. We didn't dine here but the food looked amazing. It is close to the Opera. Definitely recommend to have an evening drink prior to dinner. The US Grant centennial manhattan was very good.

data.title: Delicious breakfast!
data.text:
My husband and I stopped by for breakfast today. We normally frequent the Grant Grill about every month or so...I ordered the Croque Madame and my husband ordered French Toast with a side of bacon. We also had 2 glasses of orange juice and 2 coffees. Total price with tip was 71 dollars plus change. The breakfast was fine, although one of the eggs on my Croque Madame was over cooked. I asked the waiter to return the meal (which I rarely do); the second time was much better.  Food was delicious, the Bechamel sauce on the Croque Madame was very good as was the side of asparagus. The Grant Grill is a very nice place and overall the hotel is beautiful. The employees are very friendly and efficient.  Service is always very good. I would definitely return to this restaurant.
Tip-if you use the valet parking it is free for at least 3 hours. Not sure if this is all the time-would check with the hotel.

data.title: Dining
data.text: If you are enjoying downtown San Diego, CA stop by the US Grant Hotel. Their restaraunt Grant's Grill is top notch! The food is great and the service is excellent. Great for an anniversary.

data.title: Bad service
data.text: Perhaps this was just a bad experience... Bad luck... Food and atmosphere were excellent. Unfortunately the server was not helpful in helping us male choice: all he would say is people order this or that. Service was hovering : filling glasses of water constantly as soon as someone had two sips, ready to take plates off as soon as someone put their utensils down even though not all were finished, and they even put place serting for the bext cover while someone at table was in the middle of their plate, reaching over and impairing her to eat. The server was loud and kepr interrupting our conversation instead of waiting to do his job. It felt more like he was serving in a sports bar than at a dressed up restaurant. Otherwise everything was excellent, so it is a real shame... Or real bad luck...

data.title: Outstanding rehearsal dinner venue
data.text: The family had a private room reserved for our son's wedding rehearsal dinner. The experience was wonderful. The staff was attentive, friendly and very professional. Everyone found their meals to be excellent from a simple burger and fries chosen by the kids to various seafood dishes ordered by adults. The head waiter was highly attentive and helpful in coordinating the opening of the wedding flutes  by the couple and serving the champagne for toasting. Many thanks to the Grant Grill for assisting in making the rehearsal dinner a success.

data.title: Great selection
data.text: Herb marinated shrimp was great with pesto sauce. Crab cake with mango was best crab  cake i had. Fries with cheese top was best hit with rest of family.

user_location.name: San Juan Capistrano, California, United States

data.title: Excellent cocktails and artful food
data.text: We enjoyed a round of house invented cocktails that were truly unique and quite good. We ordered some appetizers and they were artfully presented and delicious. Only issue was that the bartender forget to serve our second round, so we quietly decided to skip them and paid our check. I didn't really want to pay $47 for forgotten cocktails. Don't let that faze you though. No one is perfect, but the drinks he did make were superb.

data.title: Perfect in every way
data.text: I hosted a small (6 people) birthday dinner here. I cannot say enough about how wonderful the entire experience was. The ambiance is elegant, quiet, sophisticated. The service is attentive and personal without ever being intrusive. The food -- all of it -- is perfectly prepared and seasoned. The wine list is excellent. If you enjoy fine dining in what I would call an "old" traditional style, you will LOVE the Grant Grill. The party I am describing was one year ago, and I am still thinking about that magical evening.

data.title: Superb Way to Start Your Day!
data.text: While we weren't impressed with our suite at the US Grant Hotel but the Grant Grill was exceptional.  We enjoyed both breakfast and lunch during our stay.  The setting is elegant.  The staff is warm and attentive.  And the cuisine is creative, perfectly presented, and delightfully delicious.  Focusing on breakfast, I had the Pork Belly Benedict.  Slices of smoked pork belly atop medallions of corn bread with a rich hollandaise sauce.  Garnished with watercress and herbs, it was unique, flavorful and a symphony of taste and texture.  My husband enjoyed the Summer Squash Quiche. Zucchini, corn, bacon, spinach, aged cheddar, parmesan, and shallots served in a pie wedge with a melt-in-your mouth buttery crust.  Lovely.  Both dishes were accompanied by the house twice-cooked potatoes.  Baby Yukon golds baked, torn in half, and then flash fried.  Decadent but worth the calories.  What a superb way to start your day.  We'll be back....not for the hotel, but certainly for the Grant Grill!

data.title: 2 visits - one excellent, one poor
data.text:
We have just returned from a 6 night stay at the hotel. We visited the grill twice. Our first visit was superb. The exceptional service from both the maître d and bar man made the visit. The bar was full when we arrived due to a pre theatre crowd but we were made welcome and we were quickly made comfortable. The cocktails were superb and we enjoyed chatting with the bar man as he made them. A really great experience. 

We returned a couple of days later (last Friday). There was live jazz on in the bar, which was lovely. We ordered wine (again great.) Unfortunately this visit was somewhat spoiled by poor customer service. We ordered the cheese and meat platter to accompany our drinks. When it arrived it was underwhelming and not as described in the menu. The menu suggested there would be different meats, in fact there was just one ridiculously small piece of ham.   The cheese was a described however the piece of blue cheese was just the rind, the actual cheese was no longer there (it looked eaten, but I am sure it wasn't, I imagine it had dropped off whilst being plated).   It was not a great concern just a little disappointing, we continued to enjoy our evening. The issue came when the waitress came over to enquire if we were enjoying our meal. I didn't intend to complain, but seeing as she asked I explained the issues. She responded in a very abrupt way. She said sometimes the platter comes as described, sometimes it doesn't, it depends what they have in the kitchen (?). She said she would feedback my comment about the strange non-piece of blue cheese. She thanked us for our feedback, apparently it is always useful, and then she abruptly left.  This is not the response I expected in a luxury hotel. The staff from the previous evening were not there that night, I would imagine they would have been a lot more responsive. 

We did order room service during our stay and the food was excellent, so this inconsistent level of service was disappointing. We intended to dine at the Grill the next evening, but following this negative experience we decided to go elsewhere.

data.title: Best breakfast on our trip
data.text: I had the egg sandwich with potatoes. It was amazing! Loved it spent a long time trying to eat it all but finally gave up. Two people had grants breakfast and one bagel/lox. Everyone loved their meals.

data.title: Service suffers if crowded
data.text: My parents took my wife and I to this restaurant since they have had so many great times and food there.  Unfortunately, when we went there it was opening night at the Civic Theater nearby.  The place was packed.  it took 30 minutes for drinks, then they got my mother's order wrong and the pork cheeks, according to my parents, were not as good as usual.  Finally, it took ages to get the bill and pay.  Apparently there were some staff issues, but for a restaurant of this price range, you have to be able to do well at ALL times.

data.title: Actualize your information
data.text: We are not from SD, even the hostest was kind we realized that dinner was closed, you should actualize your information on trip advisor too, not only on your website.

data.title: Upscale, but comfortable
data.text: Whether dining for brunch, dinner or drinks and apps, Grant Grill will not disappoint.  Something for everyone on the carefully selected menu.  Food prepared and presented to appeal to any gourmand.

data.title: Beautiful with Great Service
data.text:
This bistro is beautifully decorated with great, warm ambience.

The menu is diverse and the food excellent.

Service was fantastic.

data.title: Private dinner. Lovely service and food
data.text: The building is beautiful. Fancy  and reminiscent of an earlier era. We had a private room and the service was incredible. Friendly and attentive. A hard combination to find. Food was presented artfully and also tasty. Had the Romaine hearts salad and tenderloin with chanterelles. Both excellent.

data.title: Healthy breakfast in this wonderful historic hotel!
data.text: We loved this place! This historic hotel is gorgeous and well maintained. The dining room was very comfortable and we were pleased with the large teapot we were served at our table for our regular morning green tea. The Power  Breakfast was perfect, and very flavorful and healthy.  The Buttermilk Pancakes with fresh blueberries and citrus mascarpone topping were terrific, too. Can't wait to come back on our next trip to San Diego.

data.title: Excellent Food & Cocktails - outstanding services
data.text: This was a great place for drinks/appetizers in the evening and the breakfast was awesome.  We didn't have a full sit down dinner.  Breakfast was excellent.
